'''Henry Noel Humphreys''' (1810–1879),<ref>See [[s:Humphreys, Henry Noel (DNB00)|Humphreys, Henry Noel]], in Dictionary of National Biography, 1885-1900, Volume 28.</ref> was a [[United Kingdom of Great Britain and Ireland|British]] illustrator, [[naturalist]], [[entomologist]], and [[numismatist]].
Humphreys, who studied [[List of illuminated manuscripts|medieval manuscripts]] in Italy as a young man, became an accomplished scholar in numerous subjects. In addition to his [[Entomology|entomological]] texts, Humphreys wrote works on ancient [[Ancient Greek coinage|Greek]] and [[Ancient Rome|Roman]] [[coins]], [[archaeology]], and the art of [[calligraphy|writing]] and [[printing]].<ref name=PrincetonGraphic2010>{{cite web|last1=Mellby|first1=Julie L.|title=Humphreys' Papier-Mâché Bindings|url=https://blogs.princeton.edu/graphicarts/2010/01/humphreys_papier-mache_binding.html|website=Graphic Arts|publisher=Princeton University Library|accessdate=19 January 2016}}</ref>
