'''ʿAbd al-Ra’ūf ibn Tāj al-ʿArifīn al-Munāwī''' (also ''al-Manawī''; b. AH 952 / AD 1545; d. AH 1031 / AD 1621) was an [[Ottoman Egypt|Ottoman period]] Islamic scholar of [[Cairo]], known for his works on the [[early history of Islam]] and the history of [[Sufism]] in Egypt. He was a disciple of [[al-Sha`rani]]. Author of ''Tawqīf ʿalā Muhammāt al-Taʿārīf''.
==Works== *'' Fayd al-Qadir Sharh al-Jami` al-Saghir'' (ed. Beirut: Dar al-Ma‘rifah), commentary on the ''Jami`'' by [[Imam al-Suyuti]]
==References== *{{EI2|volume=7|author1=Johannes Hendrik Kramers|author2=Joseph Schacht|page=565}}
