{{Use dmy dates|date=September 2018}} {{short description|Soviet writer, historian and poet}} {{BLP sources|date=February 2017}}
[[File:Uladzimir Arlow Polack.jpg|thumb|right|240px|Uładzimier Arłou in 2010]] [[File:Uładzimir Arłou 25.03.2016.png|thumb|right|240px|Uładzimir Arłou's signature]]
'''Uładzimir Arłou''', known by pseudonym '''U. A. Arlou''' ([[Belarusian language|Belarusian]]:Уладзімір Аляксеевіч Арлоў, also known as Vladimir Aljaseevich Orlov, [[Russian language|Russian]]:Владимир Алексеевич Орлов; born 25 August 1953 in [[Polotsk]], [[Belarus]], [[Soviet Union]]) is a Belarusian historian, writer, politician, and poet.<ref name="Łuba 2000">{{cite book | last = Łuba | first = W. | title = Kto jest kim w Białorusi | publisher = Podlaski Instytut Wydawniczy | series = Biblioteka Centrum Edukacji Obywatelskiej Polska-Białoruś | year = 2000 | isbn = 978-83-913780-0-7 | url = https://books.google.com/books?id=D0MXAQAAIAAJ | language = pl | access-date = 18 September 2018 | page = 195 }}</ref> He is chairman of the Belarusian [[PEN International]].
== Early life and career == Arłou attended in 1970 at middle school in Polotsk and in 1975, he studied history at the [[Belarusian State University]] in [[Minsk]]. He was a history teacher in the school [[Navapolatsk]] from 1976 until 1986. He also worked as a [[contributing editor]] and correspondent for the [[newspaper]] ''Chimik'' (Хімік). Since 1988, he was working as a lector in the publishing company ''Mastazkaja Litaratura'' (Мастацкая літаратура). Since 1986, Arlou has been a member of Belorussian writer's association. In 1988, during the period of [[Perestroika]], that he joined the Belarusian Popular Front ([[BPF Party]]). In 1989 he resigned from the KPdSU. In 1992, he moved to the Belorussian Parliament twice as a deputy of BNP. Since 1997, Arlou has been working as an editor in the editoral board of the journal magazine ''Kryniza'' (Крыніца). His poems were published since 1976, first in the Almanachen ''Blakitny lichtar'' (Блакітны ліхтар) and ''Milavisa'' (Мілавіца). Beside his poems among other things a historical ethnographic work. In 1986, he was awarded for the Lenin Komsomol of Belarus for his novel ''Dobry dsen, maya Shypshyna (Добры дзень, мая Шыпшына)''.
== Personal life == Arlou is married to his wife and also has two sons. In 2010, he was honored in [[Gdańsk]], [[Poland]] with literary prize "European Poet of Freedom" (Europejski Poeta Wolności).<ref>{{Cite web | url = http://www.europejskipoetawolnosci.pl/pl/aktualnosci/europejski_poeta_wolnosci_wybrany | title = Europejski poeta wolności | access-date = 29 March 2010 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20100412071544/http://www.europejskipoetawolnosci.pl/pl/aktualnosci/europejski_poeta_wolnosci_wybrany | archive-date = 12 April 2010 | dead-url = yes | df = }}</ref>
