'''Zikmund Winter''' (27 December 1846 - 12 June 1912) was a [[Czech Republic|Czech]] writer and historian. The author of many [[historical novel]]s and essays, he maintained an interest in [[Bohemian]] life from the fifteenth to seventeenth centuries. He died in 1912 and he was buried in [[Vinohrady Cemetery]].<ref name=grave>[http://www.myczechrepublic.com/prague/vinohrady-cemeteries.html Vinohrady Cemeteries], MyCzechRepublic.com, retrieved 20 November 2013</ref>
